Ahead of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Osun State Governorship Primary election slated for Monday, March 7th, 2022, the party national leaders has revealed plans to meet stakeholders and all aspirants. Recall that, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has fixed July 16, 2022, for the Osun State governorship election. The meeting of PDP leaders and Osun stakeholders will take place tomorrow, Tuesday, February 1st, 2022 at the NEC Hall, PDP National Headquarters, Wadata Plaza, Abuja. The PDP National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba told our correspondent on Monday, that all party stakeholders and aspirants are expected to attend the crucial meeting. Aspirants expected at the meeting include the PDP 2018 candidate, Senator Ademola Adeleke, Dr Akin Ogunbiyi, Omirin Emmanuel Olusanya, Dele Adeleke, former Secretary to Osun State Government, Abdulateef Akinbade and Mr Dotun Babayemi.